<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Junie on maiatoday</title><link>https://www.maiatoday.net/categories/junie/</link><description>Recent content in Junie on maiatoday</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 09 Jun 2025 12:52:55 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.maiatoday.net/categories/junie/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Is it vaporwave? - Compose Hot reload</title><link>https://www.maiatoday.net/p/is-it-vaporwave-compose-hot-reload/</link><pubDate>Mon, 09 Jun 2025 12:52:55 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://www.maiatoday.net/p/is-it-vaporwave-compose-hot-reload/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://www.maiatoday.net/p/is-it-vaporwave-compose-hot-reload/vapor.png" alt="Featured image of post Is it vaporwave? - Compose Hot reload" /&gt;&lt;h2 id="why"&gt;Why
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;I want to play with the recently released &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.jetbrains.com/help/kotlin-multiplatform-dev/compose-hot-reload.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Compose Hot reload feature&lt;/a&gt; by JetBrains. To do this I setup a Desktop compose project and picked a topic to draw and explore: &lt;a class="link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaporwave" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Vaporwave&lt;/a&gt; Why? because Vaporwave is a curious Internet thing. It has a strong visual aesthetic that I wanted to recreate. It is intriguing. It is seems to be a fleeting transient phenomena: it is in the name &lt;em&gt;vapor&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;wave&lt;/em&gt; and yet&amp;hellip; and yet we see it &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.aesdes.org/2025/01/23/vaporwave/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;pop&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.creativeboom.com/insight/why-vaporwave-is-set-to-be-a-huge-design-trend-in-2023/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;up&lt;/a&gt; in unexpected &lt;a class="link" href="https://rausgegangen.de/en/events/vaporwave-paradise-vaporwave-fest-cologne-0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;places&lt;/a&gt;. It is a form of &lt;a class="link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hauntology#:~:text=Hauntology%20%28a%20portmanteau%20of%20haunting,if%20to%20haunt%20the%20present." target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;hauntology&lt;/a&gt;: a cultural idea that returns from the past to haunt the present.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be ramblings interspersed and remixed with code, I will put the code at the beginning of the sections, so that you can easily skim if remix-rambling is not your thing. Yes, there is a &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;matching repo&lt;/a&gt;. Yes, it is a mix of organic hand coding and AI enhancements. I will &lt;a class="link" href="#enter-the-ais" &gt;explain my process&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But first&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="setting-up-hot-reload"&gt;Setting up Hot Reload
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A project that has a Compose desktop part. It can be stand alone or part of a multiplatform project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use a Kotlin version 2.1.20 or later&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get the &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/JetBrains/compose-hot-reload" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;plugin and the latest version information&lt;/a&gt; and add it the place you keep your versions, like a toml file&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setup the plugin in your build.gradle.kts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setup the foojay resolver&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the main application from the gutter icon or command line. something like &lt;code&gt;./gradlew runHot --mainClass MainKt --auto&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optional extra make a run target for your particular main application if you have more than one
See and &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/howToAddHotReload.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;example&lt;/a&gt; of each line in the sample repo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wow these instructions are vague!&lt;/em&gt; indeed things change quickly. Please follow the original repo. This post will date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="origins-and-sound-track"&gt;Origins and Sound track
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vaporwave appeared as a music genre with a strong aesthetic, some say in 2010. The iconic album &lt;a class="link" href="https://vektroid.bandcamp.com/album/floral-shoppe" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Floral Shoppe by Macintosh Plus&lt;/a&gt; is still available and makes a perfect sound track for inspecting the code or reading this article.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Go ahead click the &lt;a class="link" href="https://vektroid.bandcamp.com/album/floral-shoppe" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;link&lt;/a&gt; and start the music. I&amp;rsquo;ll wait.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are on the cusp of widespread changes in how we interact with technology. Will we have nostalgia for the way we did thing in the &lt;em&gt;olden days&lt;/em&gt;? Will we even remember how it really was?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="a-e-s-t-h-e-t-i-c"&gt;A-E-S-T-H-E-T-I-C
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vaporwave is known for a strong aesthetic. Here is a jumpstart table with the technique and a note. &lt;strong&gt;Click on the image to see the code&lt;/strong&gt; or scroll for more detail&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Image&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Techniques&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Notes&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/Triangle.kt#L26"&gt;&lt;img src="triangle.png" alt="triangle" width="100"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/Triangle.kt#L26" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Path on Canvas, Linear gradient brush&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Triangles are geometric shapes reminiscent of corporate logos of the eighties: an abstract shape that becomes a place holder for ambiguous concepts like digital consumerism&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/VanishingFloor.kt#L37"&gt;&lt;img src="floorgrid.png" alt="floorgrid" width="100"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/VanishingFloor.kt#L37" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Canvas, Offset and Path, conversion of Offset to create perspective&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;a magenta grid looks like something from a pixelated game: a technology that we recognise and remember imperfectly with nostalgia. It also has a black and white tiled version.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/utils/ImageFromPath.kt#L28"&gt;&lt;img src="colorshift.png" alt="colorshift" width="100"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/utils/ImageFromPath.kt#L28" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Image with a BitmapPainter, ColorFilter, colorMatrix, blur,&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;The choice of pngs, dolphins and old tech cassettes. Greek sculptures to remind us of beauty ideals. Having these elements floating makes them look surreal. Using blur and color filters change what they look like to simulate old VHS errors. Remembering past technology imperfectly. Human and digital memory is fallable.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/Sunset.kt#L25"&gt;&lt;img src="sunset.png" alt="sunset" width="100"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/Sunset.kt#L25" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;drawCircle filled with gradients with color stops and Color.Transparent&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;a retro sunset in a perfect world remembered imperfectly&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/NeonPalm.kt#L20"&gt;&lt;img src="palm.png" alt="palm" width="100"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/aesthetic/NeonPalm.kt#L20" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
