&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;0.74f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;Color&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Transparent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;0.74f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;middleColor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;0.84f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bottomColor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;0.84f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;Color&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Transparent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;0.9f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;Color&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Transparent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;0.9f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bottomColor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;1.0f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bottomColor&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;),&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;startY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;0f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;endY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;height&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="palm-tree-svg"&gt;Palm tree svg
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img src="palm.png" alt="Sunset" width="200"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is possible to extract the points of a simple svg. Looking at the sample &lt;a class="link" href="p3.svg" &gt;palm tree file&lt;/a&gt; find the following line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src="svg-points.png" alt="Sunset" width="500"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Copy the string into the code and convert it to a Path. The problem is the points are relative to the coordinate system and size of the svg image and not the resulting composable view. It needs to be transformed. The conversion is based on the original path and the destination composable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The conversion code looks like this&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;fromBoundsToComposeView&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bounds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Rect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Rect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mf"&gt;1f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mf"&gt;1f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;1f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mf"&gt;1f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;),&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;width&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Float&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;height&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Float&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Matrix&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="py"&gt;originalWidth&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bounds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;right&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bounds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;left&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="py"&gt;originalHeight&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bounds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;bottom&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bounds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;top&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="py"&gt;scale&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;min&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;width&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;originalWidth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;height&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;originalHeight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="py"&gt;newLeft&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bounds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;left&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;width&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;scale&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;originalWidth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="py"&gt;newTop&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bounds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;top&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;height&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;scale&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;originalHeight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="py"&gt;matrix&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Matrix&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;matrix&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;translate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;newLeft&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;newTop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;matrix&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;scale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;scale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;scale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;matrix&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Apply the resulting matrix to the image. &lt;code&gt;path.transform(matrix)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="mesh-gradient"&gt;Mesh Gradient
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img src="mesh.png" alt="Mesh gradient" width="200"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a really useful &lt;a class="link" href="https://gist.github.com/sinasamaki/05725557c945c5329fdba4a3494aaecb" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;mesh gradient modifier&lt;/a&gt; created by sinasamaki with a great &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.sinasamaki.com/mesh-gradients-in-jetpack-compose/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;writeup&lt;/a&gt; on how it works. Hot reload is useful for tuning the colors of the gradients. There is also a &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/c5inco/Mesh" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;visual tool&lt;/a&gt; to set the gradient up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src="meshtool.png" alt="Mesh gradient" width="400"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="glitches"&gt;Glitches
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img src="glitch.png" alt="Glitch" width="200"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is possible to use &lt;a class="link" href="https://skia.org/docs/user/sksl/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Skia Shaders&lt;/a&gt; with Compose. The setup is easy enough and the shader is copied into a string. I found a &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4dXBW2" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;small glitch shader by Coolok&lt;/a&gt; on ShaderToy. Integration is &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/62643066a19564a06507ef86a399aead1527994e/src/main/kotlin/utils/GlitchShader.kt#L126" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;straight forward&lt;/a&gt; by creating a runtime Shader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding shader code is something else entirely. The core understanding is that shader code runs on a single pixel position not on the whole image. So the code has to make changes from the pixel perspective. The main entry point is &lt;code&gt;mainImage&lt;/code&gt;. You get the pixel coordinates in a two dimensional vector, &lt;code&gt;fragCoord&lt;/code&gt; and the code has to return the color of the pixel at that position in a four dimensional vector (RGBA) in &lt;code&gt;fragColor&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hot reload is a useful tool to tweak and experiment with shaders to learn how they work. &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGmrMu-IwbguU_nY2egTFmlg691DN7uE5" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;This playlist&lt;/a&gt;, on learning how to build shaders on ShaderToy, is a good resource to get started.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="enter-the-ais"&gt;Enter the AIs
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Of course I had help - &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.jetbrains.com/junie/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Junie&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.jetbrains.com/ai-assistant/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;AI assistent&lt;/a&gt; as well as &lt;a class="link" href="https://gemini.google.com/app" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Gemini&lt;/a&gt; for research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="research-with-gemini"&gt;Research with Gemini
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;To orient me and to be sure I understood vaporwave, Gemini did a deep research &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/docs/vaporwave.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;report&lt;/a&gt; on the topic for me. I AI-slop created the pixelated cassettes, palm outlines and the marble statue image in Gemini.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="plans-and-execution-with-junie"&gt;Plans and execution with Junie
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;make a list of &lt;em&gt;compose techniques&lt;/em&gt; to explore&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;make a list of &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/docs/look/aesthetics.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;vaporwave aesthetic elements&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;create a &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/README.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;readme&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/.junie/guidelines.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;guidelines&lt;/a&gt; file&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;collect visual references, blog posts with code snippets, bitmaps, images, fonts and colours in a &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/docs/look" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;docs folder&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;take each of the aesthetic elements and ask Junie to &lt;em&gt;build&lt;/em&gt; one sample element and use it in a specific composable e.g.
&lt;code&gt;Build an equilateral triangle composable that draws on the Canvas and uses a gradient brush. Show and example of this composable in the SoloTriangle composable&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;check, commit, tag and goto step 5&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;rsquo;t let Junie just do the whole list. I prompted each element separately so that I could check it out and tweak it before I commited and tagged. I also started a fresh context and a new task for each step. This worked well because the &lt;code&gt;guidelines.md&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;docs/look&lt;/code&gt; folder kept the continuity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="inbetween-questions-with-ai-assistant"&gt;Inbetween questions with AI assistant
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;While Junie was busy building things, I use the AI assistant to research info with oneshot questions for the next task. e.g.
&lt;code&gt;How do I draw a perspective grid that has a single vanishing point on a flat surface&lt;/code&gt;
The answer was python code. I asked it to &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/docs/look/perspective.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;explain&lt;/a&gt; the python code. The chat session didn&amp;rsquo;t interfere with what Junie was doing. In my next prompt to Junie, I asked it to use the research I captured in a markdown file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="understanding-everything-with-deepwiki"&gt;Understanding everything with DeepWiki
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;For more detailed understanding of the whole project, I fed it to &lt;a class="link" href="https://deepwiki.com/maiatoday/vapor" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;DeepWiki&lt;/a&gt;. This helped to make sense of some opaque parts such as the &lt;a class="link" href="https://deepwiki.com/maiatoday/vapor/5.2-glitch-effect" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;glitch shader code&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="all-the-things"&gt;All the things
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The final composition of all the pieces is a quick and dirty &lt;code&gt;Box&lt;/code&gt; or two with everything inside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A fun way to showcase hot reload is to run the app, in my case&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;./gradlew runHot --mainClass MainKt --auto&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then in a separate terminal run the &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/maiatoday/vapor/blob/main/speedrun.kts" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;speedrun&lt;/a&gt; script. This script checks out a git tag in a series of git tags when you type enter in the terminal. Because the app is running auto updating hot reload, the changes appear progressively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tada!
